<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Saarem on 05-26-2002 06:27 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">When was the last time you saw a resisted CH?
When was the last time you saw a resisted snare?
When was the last time you saw a raid say, damn, we cant do this due to lack of snarers?
When was the last time you saw a person get resisted CH can not land in any way (you can remove the balance curse) message?
When was the last time you saw a raid called of due to lacking druids or had a raid tell 3 people to log on their boot druids to make the raid happend?

CH is the bane and blessing for clerics. Due to CH so can we heal ALOT better then anyone else and are the only once who can stand up to healing on a boss mob but it also held above us as the reason to never get anything but nerfs due to the power of it. And no, there aint often you do dot up mobs because they mobs dont live long enough. And assuming you do dot them up so do you have 15 slots total for all debuffs and dots to land and a single necro can easy fill them (not counting for all procs with dot etc).

How many other classes ingame can you not do a raid if you only got 1 or 0? 1 warrior is enough, you can have paladins/SKs on rampage instead with right AA, slow can be done by enchanter, same with cripple. Manasong covers that, speed by song/shaman etc. But you can never, ever, replace the four clerics in the CH chain. Say we take druids as are the best direct healers short of cleric, say they use NTs 880hp heal. Say our average CH is 3k, that would mean ~3x the druids to heal at the exact same time as we would CH, but not only that, that only takes care of average healing. Sometimes mobs get a lucky run on hits + flurry and thet CH did 6k instead of healing, so now we need 7x the druids to do the healing. So now we are standing here with 28+ druids to do the job of 4 clerics and they all have to time it exactly and that is not accounting for the extra lag from it. If we take a normal raiding force so would we instead of having the average 44 people there so would we with druids healing have 68 people. Now that is quite a bump in lag. If you do the math on shamans so would it be even worse due to lower direct heal.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
